# TODO

- Revisit the FlexFEC default
  Browser support is still narrower than for TWCC, NACK, and RTX. Confirm whether FlexFEC should remain an explicit opt-in.

- Evaluate additional adaptive bitrate backends
  `twcc-gcc` is the current default. Add new backends only if there is a clear operational use case.

- Evaluate a second-stage adaptation step
  Resolution or frame-rate changes may be useful for single-viewer deployments. The current implementation only adjusts encoder bitrate.

- Improve the AV1 path
  Revisit encoder settings, latency, and shutdown behavior before treating AV1 as equivalent to the H264 path.
